              "text": "2790 - "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "رَوَى اَلْحُسَيْنُ بْنُ سَعِيدٍ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "إِسْمَاعِيلَ بْنِ هَمَّامٍ اَلْمَكِّيِّ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/1969",
              "text": "أَبِي اَلْحَسَنِ اَلرِّضَا"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "أَبِيهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:65:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/65/1",
        "text": [
          " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : «فِي اَلَّذِي عَلَيْهِ اَلْمَشْيُ إِذَا رَمَى اَلْجَمْرَةَ زَارَ اَلْبَيْتَ رَاكِباً»."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2790 - Al-Husayn ibn Sa‘id narrated from Isma‘il ibn Hammam al-Makki, from Abu al-Hasan al-Ridha (as), from his father (as), who said: Abu Abdullah (as) said:\n\"For someone obligated to walk [during the Hajj rituals], if they have thrown pebbles at the Jamrah, they may visit the Kaaba (for tawaf) while riding.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1224,
        "local_index": 2,
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:65:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/65/2",
        "text": [
          "2791 - وَ رُوِيَ : «أَنَّ مَنْ نَذَرَ أَنْ يَمْشِيَ إِلَى بَيْتِ اَللَّهِ حَافِياً مَشَى فَإِذَا تَعِبَ رَكِبَ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2791 - It is narrated: \"Whoever makes a vow to walk to the House of Allah (swt) barefoot should walk, but if they become tired, they may ride.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1225,
        "local_index": 3,
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:65:3",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/65/3",
        "text": [
          "2792 - وَ رُوِيَ : «أَنَّهُ يَمْشِي مِنْ خَلْفِ اَلْمَقَامِ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2792 - It is narrated: \"They should walk from behind the Maqam (Station of Ibrahim).\""
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
